ary in Japan's space capabilities and policy. This book shows how the sum total of market-to-military moves across space launch vehicles, satellites and spacecraft, and emerging related technologies, already mark Japan as an advanced military space power.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aAstronautics and statezJapan. 0aAstronautics, MilitaryzJapan. 0aNational securityzJapan. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Freedom.2bisacsh1 aKallender-Umezu, Paul, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804775007zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804775007423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804775007.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles